s who volunteered to oppose the British invasion of New Haven in 1779. He graduated in the class of 1779."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"Land agent and innkeeper on the Pennsylvania frontier","body":"After Yale, Welles settled at Athens on the Pennsylvania frontier as agent for the Carroll lands and proprietor of the Athens Hotel. He grew rich in valuable lands and served as a justice of the peace."},{"number":3,"category":"death","header":"He died in the Sheshequin fever epidemic","body":"In 1813 a deadly epidemic the settlers called the 'Sheshequin fever' swept Tioga Point, striking only adults and sparing no one under fifteen. George Welles was among its victims, buried in late June at the height of the outbreak."}],"sources":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"George","last_name":"Welles","married_names":[],"display_name":"George Welles","gender":"male","bio_blurb":"Yale-educated Pennsylvania land agent and innkeeper"},"military_service":[],"education":[{"school_name":"Yale College","dates":"1779","type":"undergraduate","notes":"Class of 1779."}],"career":[{"role":"Land agent","organization":"Carroll lands, Athens PA","notes":"Agent for the Carroll estate."},{"role":"Innkeeper","organization":"Athens Hotel","start_year":1798,"end_year":1809},{"role":"Justice of the peace","organization":"Athens, Pennsylvania"}],"slug":"george-welles-1756"},"T01019":{"id":"T01019","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1757,"month":12,"day":2,"city":"Glastonbury","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1839,"month":11,"day":20,"city":"Owego","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"burial":{},"residence":{"city":"Glastonbury","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"classification":{"is_t